solution.p:
For Kent County, the population in 1990 was 500,631 and in 2010 was 602,622, so

  AV_{[1990,2010]} &= \frac{602{,}622 - 500{,}631}{2010 - 1990}
  &= \frac{101{,}991}{20}
  &\approx 5099.55 \text{ people per year.}

For Ottawa County, the population in 1990 was 187,768 and in 2010 was 263,801, so

  AV_{[1990,2010]} &= \frac{263{,}801 - 187{,}768}{2010 - 1990}
  &= \frac{76{,}033}{20}
  &\approx 3801.65 \text{ people per year.}
